articles.title: After years of struggle, Tel Aviv University will remove the name Sackler from the Faculty of Medicine - Haaretz
articles.description: This article discusses the decision by Tel Aviv University to remove the name of the family behind the pharmaceutical company responsible for the opioid epidemic in the US from their medical faculty. The family has agreed to the removal in order to allow the university to find new donors without fear of legal action. The article also provides background on the family's involvement in the opioid epidemic and recent legal settlements.

articles.author: הידען
articles.title: The robot that will recognize intentions - The National Science Foundation - The Science
articles.description: This article discusses the development of robotic arms that can assist users based on their movements and needs. The technology relies on algorithms, artificial intelligence, cameras, and sensors to process information and perform tasks. The researchers aim to create affordable and accessible robots that can aid in various tasks, such as household chores, medical procedures, and heavy lifting. The robotic arms are controlled by a sleeve worn by the user, which communicates with a computer that controls the arm's movements. The researchers have conducted successful experiments demonstrating the arm's ability to assist with various tasks.

articles.title: N12 - Reinforcement of forces and targeted activity: The houses of the terrorists who carried out... - mako were mapped
articles.description: This article reports on security forces' actions in the village of Urif in response to the recent shooting attack near the settlement of Eli, in which four Israelis were killed. The forces are conducting investigations, searches, and mapping of the homes of the terrorists involved in the attack. One of the suspects arrested is the brother of the terrorist who carried out the attack. The article also describes retaliatory actions taken by Jewish settlers in the village of Luban, including attacks on Palestinian homes and businesses. The article warns of the potential for further violence and calls for increased security measures to protect residents.

articles.title: Bacteria resistant to antibiotics were found in streams in Israel - voila! health
articles.description: This article discusses a new Israeli study that found polluted streams may be a breeding ground for antibiotic-resistant bacteria that can also spread to the sea. The article also highlights the growing problem of antibiotic-resistant bacteria and how they adapt to different treatments, making them difficult to treat. The study used a new method to analyze the genetic material of bacteria found in a polluted stream to understand their origins and potential impact.

articles.description: This article discusses the recent correction in the S&P 500 index and how it has affected local investment products. Local savings and investment products that track the index have seen a significant increase in returns, with some offering double-digit returns. However, experts caution that market behavior is unpredictable and other indices may become more popular in the future. Passive investment products are becoming more popular globally, but Israel lags behind in this trend. Various investment firms offer a range of passive and active investment products, with some offering exposure to specific sectors such as technology.
